In creating a system that we expect players to be able to role-play satisfactorily it must tie in with the world we have created and the ideas we have developed.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs24 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2.\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\faauto\ls1\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
Playability
\par }\pard \qj \li360\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 As with any mud, death and dying can often be a difficult and ambiguous part 
of mud life. It is best to devise a system by which players do not lose their characters permanently upon dying within the mud. At the same time death still needs to be seen as a negative thing, so penalties should apply. It is important that these penalt
ies help to dissuade players from treating death lightly.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs24 
\par So basically our system needs to fit in with the world, but allow players to continue to use their characters despite dying in various situations. 
\par 
\par At the moment the system is only partially implemented, if that. There is some code in place that when you die you become a \'93ghost\'94 and you can reform at any time. You can also \'93haunt\'94 people whilst you are a ghost.
\par 
\par The whole idea of ghosts and ectoplasm and poltergeists is not an idea that fits with the mud. This document will aim to better describe death on Lu\rquote Tamohr as I see it.
\par 
\par 
\par When you die, your spirit element is separated from the rest of your elemental makeup i.e. your physical self. Whether you die because your head was chopped off, or from poi
son, death is a reaction  which causes your spirit element to become separated from the rest of you because basically your physical self can no longer continue.
\par 
\par Whilst you are only the part of you made up by your spirit element you experience a strange \'93new\'94 world. It\rquote s the same world really, but you can\rquote 
t talk or interact with the living or the dead. You can see the living, but you cant hear them or talk to them or see what they are doing (emotes) you just know there is a living person there in contrast t
o what you are which is not wholly living. You cant use magic, or your skills, you are a pale comparison to your former self. You also cant communicate with other \'93spirits\'94
 except in extreme circumstances through outside intervention. Powerful mages can enter spirit form and setup communication with other spirits, but typically you cant do anything except watch.
\par 
\par On the other side the living cannot see you, except for those with powerful magic able to use that to see your spirit self and in some cases do more then see (e.g. bind your spirit, reform you etc)
\par 
\par 
\par Luckily, thanks to the wonderful advances in magic, if your spirit element is pure enough you can be \'93rebuilt\'94 and restored to life. When I say pure enough there are a number of ways in which the purity of your spirit-element makeup can be affected.

\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\faauto\ls2\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
The older you are, the less pure it becomes.  
\par }\pard \qj \li360\ri0\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 Each time you become separated part of your spirit \'93leaks\'94
 out as a side affect of the untangling of the other elements in your body from your spirit element.
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\faauto\ls2\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
The longer you stay as a spirit the less pure your spirit becomes.
\par }\pard \qj \li360\ri0\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 Over time whilst in spirit form your spirit element is
 drawn or magnetized back into the overall elemental pool. If you are restored quickly this effect if negligible. Once however your entire spirit has succumbed to this effect you are no more. It takes a long time in most cases to go from the stage where y
ou cannot be reformed because of too much impurity in your spirit to the stage where you are no more and it is gradual. You would lose memories etc.
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\faauto\ls2\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
Some powerful magic can damage or restore your spirits purity.
\par }\pard \qj \li360\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 This will enable players to eventually repair problems incurred from dying a lot so that they can in affect live on (well lets face it play the same char) for ever.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs24 
\par Be careful not to confuse the spirit element with our perception of what spirit means. It is a magical element, and in this case 
a very special one in that the amount and way that it is formed can actually create intelligence and the possibility of life. In theory it is possible to create living things if you know how to manipulate the spirit element properly (no one does). Think o
f the makeup of someone\rquote s spirit element to be as complex as DNA however so it is currently impossible to actually create life by magic. But it can be repaired somewhat.
\par 
\par Now, if you are reformed from your spirit back to life, the purity of your spirit will
 affect some things. Initially you will suffer from spirit sickness, a temporary thing that leaves you weak and unable to do much at all. This lasts for a finite amount of time.
\par 
\par Along with this, depending upon how pure your spirit was when you were reformed, you can suffer permanent negative affects such as affects to strength (your spirit element doesn\rquote 
t link up as effectively with the earth elements etc) or other stats. It will be possible to reverse these affects through powerful rejuvinative magic. So 
your spirits purity will basically affect your physical attributes much like age does. If your spirit element is purified these negative affects will disappear.
\par 
\par So, to recap.
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls3\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\faauto\ls3\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
You die
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls3\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\faauto\ls3\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
When you die you become a spirit
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls3\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\faauto\ls3\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
