Depending upon your spirit elements purity you are affected differently by the return
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs24 
\par 
\par This is basically the system I propose but there are a few IC or role-play implications I have not yet discussed.
\par 
\par With the discovery of magic some 200 years ago, magic has made many advances, none more so then the ability to restore life in some cases. When I say some cases, all pcs can automatically be restored (if their spirit is pure enough) but in theory the
 procedure is not always successful. The magic works by mirroring the spirit element of a person back onto the other elements that made up their person. A body is not needed, the magic relying heavily upon your spirits purity to determine the balance and 
d
esign of the other elements in your makeup. Players should be encouraged to rp dying and returning, I would be happy to see even anxious moments from loved ones a player is being attempted to be reformed as the magic might not work. It should not be rped 
as being always successful.
\par 
\par Only powerful magic users have the ability to perform this, and there are not that many around. It is also a very difficult and exhausting spell to work. As a result of this
, such resurrections are expensive. There will be a resurrection chamber in a few key areas around the world. These will be manned by several initiates who usually search out those who can and wish to be resurrected and summon their spirits to be resurrec
ted by the resident powerful mage. To accommodate this we will likely have some sort of command that players in spirit form can operate to let nearby resurrection chambers know they could use some help. At the moment that command is reform I think.
\par 
\par 
\par When resurrected you appear naked in the resurrection chamber before the mage / initiates who performed the magic. I would like to see a prog made so that someone cant be resurrected until the previous person resurrected has left the room so we don
\rquote t have awkwar
d double ups where multiple people are transferred in naked and expected to do some crappy rp. Recently resurrected people should then be offered a plain robe and ushered out of the chamber (you should be able to re enter these chambers to stop abuse and 
to give the master mage better concentration ) where the next stage of resurrection is undergone. The payment.
\par 
\par If you cannot afford the price of resurrection at the time of your resurrection your equipment is confiscated until you can come up with the mone
y. A second master mage has kindly summoned your dead body (equipment attached) using various magical information. If you pay this mage then you are able to get all your things and re-clothe yourself in one of the booths provided.
\par 
\par There will be a couple of problems associated with where people are resurrected. There are a couple of options:
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls4\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnsp120\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\faauto\ls4\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 
Allow the pc to choose where by setting a resurrection point
\par }\pard \qj \li360\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\fs24 Probably the best option, perhaps they have to pay gold for an examination by the master magician who places you on file so to speak.
